@startuml Motor State Machine
!theme plain
title Motor Control State Machine\nWith Safety Features (Phases 1-2)

[*] --> STOPPED : Power-On

state "STOPPED\nGF=32 (forward)\nGF=436 (reverse)" as STOPPED {
  state "Hardware Disabled\nPD4=LOW" as HW_OFF
  state "Spindle Hold\nCL=10-12%\nPhase 2.1" as HOLD

  HW_OFF --> HOLD : HOLD command
  HOLD --> HW_OFF : RELEASE command
  HOLD : Powered position lock
  HOLD : Maintains every 460ms

  note right of HOLD
    **Spindle Hold Module**

    Manual: CL=10%, no timeout
    Safety: CL=12%, 2s timeout

    Discovered via logic analyzer
  end note
}

state "RUNNING\nGF=34 (forward)\nGF=438 (reverse)" as RUNNING {
  state "Normal Operation\nCL=100%" as NORMAL
  state "Jam Detected\nPhase 2.3" as JAM
  state "Overheat\nPhase 2.2" as OVERHEAT

  NORMAL --> JAM : Load ≥ 90%\nfor 5 seconds
  NORMAL --> OVERHEAT : Temp ≥ 80°C

  JAM : Auto-stop motor
  JAM : Send EVT_JAM_DETECTED
  OVERHEAT : Auto-stop motor
  OVERHEAT : Send EVT_OVERHEAT
}

STOPPED --> RUNNING : START command\nCL=100%, ST, SV

RUNNING --> STOPPED : STOP command\nRS=0, hardware disable

state "ERROR\nGF bit 14 set\n(≥ 16929)" as ERROR {
  state "Communication Fault\nPhase 1.1" as COMM_FAULT
  state "MCB Fault\nBit patterns" as MCB_FAULT

  note right of COMM_FAULT
    **Phase 1: Safety**

    5 consecutive comm failures
    → Trigger fault
    → Emergency stop
    → Hardware disable
  end note
}

RUNNING --> ERROR : GF response\nbit 14 set
STOPPED --> ERROR : Comm timeout

ERROR --> STOPPED : Clear fault\nReset

note right of STOPPED
  **Phase 1: Hardware Failsafe**

  If UART timeout during STOP:
  1. Log "[STOP] UART timeout"
  2. motor_hardware_disable()
     (PD4=LOW - immediate cutoff)
  3. Increment diagnostics counter

  Motor ALWAYS stops safely
end note

note bottom
  **Motor States (discovered via reverse engineering):**

  GF=32:  STOPPED, forward direction
  GF=34:  RUNNING, forward direction
  GF=436: STOPPED, reverse direction
  GF=438: RUNNING, reverse direction
  GF≥16929: ERROR state (bit 14 set)

  **Safety Features:**
  • Jam detection: Load monitoring (Phase 2.3)
  • Temperature: Threshold with hysteresis (Phase 2.2)
  • Spindle hold: Position lock (Phase 2.1)
  • UART timeout: Cannot hang (Phase 1.1)
  • Hardware failsafe: PD4 disable (Phase 1.1b)
end note

@enduml
